In both cases, the death penalty is possible, according to the document submitted to the Court.
Weeks after the attack, a federal grand jury has approved the charge with 22 charges, including eight charges of murder for a racket, typically a charge used by federal prosecutors against organized crime, and a charge of violence and destruction of motor vehicles.
